The paper discusses non-monotonic reasoning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational logic (cs.LO). The paper also focuses on complexity results for different reasoning tasks, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of fragments and restricted logical languages is also a common approach in database systems (cs.DS) and programming languages (cs.PL).
